OL,3,CTrainee PC racially abused before
OL,4,Csuicide, dad tells inquest
OL,6,FMr Abraham said, "initially" his son
OL,7,Fwas confident but admitted he was
OL,8,F"fearful" of his son joining the
OL,9,Fforce, adding: "It's a very
OL,10,Fchallenging job."
OL,12,FHis father added: "He always said
OL,13,F'nobody came to me and said, 'well
OL,14,Fdone boy''. He was always criticised.
OL,16,F"He said, 'they put me on another
OL,17,Fmanagement plan' to sack him. He was
OL,18,Funder a lot of pressure and fearful."
